						<summary>

						<p>The <hi rend="italic">Pānavaṭṭam</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">liṅga</hi> in the temple of Gōkarṇēśvara.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1134, Uttarāyaṇa.</hi> The other details are not known. This date may corresponds to 1212 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Wornout. It records the gift of 50 <hi rend="italic">inapaeḍlu</hi> (cows) probably for a perpetual lamp to the god Gōkarṇēśvara-Mahādēva. It also seems to refer to a chief called one Kēśavabhūpati and one Sītāpati.</p>						

						</summary>
